docs.abstract: To improve their services, travel companies are relying on tech to study customers’ habits, like whether they need photos of a destination before booking or decide mainly on price.
docs.snippet: To improve their services, travel companies are relying on tech to study customers’ habits, like whether they need photos of a destination before booking or decide mainly on price.
docs.lead_paragraph: At the Expedia Group product testing lab, facial recognition software gauges travelers’ feelings as they go through the process of booking hotel rooms online. The Swiss cruise company MSC Cruises is starting to use a virtual assistant to answer passengers’ questions. Designers from the boutique design and research firm the Gettys Group can show hotel executives new room layouts using virtual reality goggles, so hotels don’t need to build a full-scale model.

headline.main: A.I. Wants to Know How You Plan a Trip
headline.print_headline: Don’t Like That Room? Make a Face

docs.abstract: White-collar workers face job cuts and shrinking paychecks even in go-go industries like technology, suggesting the economic pain is broader than official figures show.
docs.snippet: White-collar workers face job cuts and shrinking paychecks even in go-go industries like technology, suggesting the economic pain is broader than official figures show.
docs.lead_paragraph: The job fair in the Chinese boomtown of Shenzhen offered a white-collar future for a country that rose to economic greatness on the strength of its assembly lines, bulldozers and cranes. Technology, financial and real estate companies pitched jobs in sales, engineering, accounting and logistics. A $150,000-a-year salary, said one poster, “isn’t just a dream.”

headline.main: China’s Slowdown Already Hit Its Factories. Now Its Offices Are Hurting, Too.

docs.lead_paragraph: Neil and Kathinka McKeown’s home in Calaveras County, Calif., burned down in a 2015 wildfire that regulators believe started when a power line made contact with a tree. Late last year, they thought they were finally close to rebuilding after reaching a seven-figure settlement with Pacific Gas & Electric, whose line was involved.

docs.lead_paragraph: Weeks after a deadly crash involving a Boeing plane last October, company officials met separately with the pilot unions at Southwest Airlines and American Airlines. The officials said they planned to update the software for their 737 Max jets, the plane involved in the disaster, by around the end of 2018.
